Stack:
Ruby 1.8.6
Rubygems 1.3.1
Rails 2.3.3
Haml
Datamapper 0.9.11
Mysql 5.X

Configure a local development instance:
Create a database called ambernet_development and grant a user access to it
Using config/database.yml.sample as an example, create your own config/database.yml

rake gems:install_custom (This is required to install a agnostic version of Mislav's will_paginate gem, you will be prompted for a sudo password)
sudo rake gems:install 
rake db:populate 

Then run with script/server!
